Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I'm on Page 04 of Hand MRI
When I select 'Finding' radio button
Then Finding dropdown menu is enabled

When I select 'Osteonecrosis' from the dropdown menu
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And a single selection localizer is enabled

When I click on the localizer
And I select 'Os scaphoideum' bone on the localizer
And I close the localizer
Then 'Edematous changes (T1w signal decrease, T2w signal increase)' radio button is enabled
And 'Changed shape with a pointed and narrow proximal pole ("nipple sign")' radio button is enabled
And 'General signal decrease of the entire bone' radio button is enabled
And 'Fragmentation' radio button is enabled

And 'Complete' radio button is enabled
And 'Partial' radio button is enabled
